uiInfo.description: One or more record IDs for the changed records. Typically, this field contains one record ID. If in one transaction the same change occurred in multiple records of the same object type during one second, Salesforce groups the change notifications. In this case, Salesforce sends one change event for all affected records and the recordIds field contains the IDs for all records that have the same change. Examples of operations with same changes are: Update of fieldA to valueA in Account records. Deletion of Account records. Renaming or replacing a picklist value that results in updating the field value in all affected records.
